@node "Intro" "Introduction"

Hi there, this is the introduction(nothing new I quess).
So, you allready started the program and still gotta "What the hell is this"
feeling? Then this is THE chapter for you!

When you're a fanzy programmer, like me, prefably assembly, and are
working with multi-source projects, you certainly need this tool!


EZMake provides you with an GUI based invironment for compiling source files
like pascal, C/C++, assembler or any programming language which needs an
external compiler callable from shell/CLI.

The advances of EZMake is that you don't have to hazzle around in the shell
to compile/link/edit/run/debug some source/executable. Just click on that
button and it happens. No need to type lots of things anymore or sticking to
that stupid limited editor with something like EZMake buildin.

More reasons to use ezmake:
 It's cool to look at it
 I use it myself
 It's bugfree
 

I have designed EZMake to be very flexible. It works with internal scripts, so
you can program a button to do whatever you want.

I know there are more project managers but they all suck because:
 it's too big (mui)
 or very limited in function
 or stupid design
 and most of them can't handle multiply commands per button


You know it: EZMake is an advanced piece of software


1 more thing:

If you're interested in project-managers but don't like ezmake or simply don't
want to register I appreciate email where you say so. It may be very short.

