@node "WindowPrefs" "WindowPrefs"

WINDOWPREFS

For each @{"list" LINK "lists"} you can set some output settings:

 o No Open  : No window will be opened, if output occuires, default output
              will be used. If you started EZMake with run >ram:xyz EZMake,
              outputs will go to ram:xyz. From workbench it's nil:.
 o No Delay : Window will be opened, command list(s) are executed
              then window is closed.
 o Wait 1   : EZMake waits 1 second before closing, giving you the
              opportunity to read the output
 o Wait 2   : idem dito (almost the same as above)
 o Wait 4   : idem dito (almost the same as above)
 o Wait 10  : idem dito (almost the same as above)
 o Wait 60  : idem dito (almost the same as above)

 BE CAREFULL WITH 'run'.
    If you run something and then its default output is closed,
    and the prog wants to output something your system will crash.

NOTE:

 SOURCES LIST    : WindowPrefs is used for the compile/make buttons
 EXECUTABLES LIST: Windowprefs is not used.



@endnode


