@node "bt_other" "other buttons"
  
buttons:
  Macro1
  Run
  Debug
  Edit
  Link

The equal named @{"list" LINK "lists"} is executed once.
@endnode
 
@node "bt_compile" "compile button"

button: Compile

One of the three compiler-script is executed, depending on
the @{"source-settings" LINK "ls_source"}
  
@endnode

@node "bt_macro2" "macro2 button"

button: Macro2
  The macro2 script will be executed FOR EACH SOURCEFILE.
@endnode

@node "bt_make" "make button"

button: Make
  This button will compile every source in the sourcelist depending on the
  source settings. Then the program is linked just like you clicked
  the Link button.
  Your programm is compiled now!
  If you show the sources in the listview you actually see the sources
  being selected one by one(and the settings too).

@endnode

@node "window" "EZMake/Global"

GLOBAL SETTINGS/Window

  Define here a window that will be opened depending on the
  @{"WindowPrefs" LINK "WindowPrefs"}. It is allowed to specify
  a file here. EXAMPLE: CON:0/0/640/200/bleh/AUTO/WAIT/CLOSE
  hmm, maby you didn't know:
    AUTO=open window visually only when output occuries
    WAIT=blocks windowclosing till user closes it. (by CTRL-\ for ex.)
    CLOSE=Add an close gadget to the window. (can be used instead of ctrl-\)

@endnode

@node "ObjectSuffix" "EZMake/ObjectSuffix"

GLOBAL SETTINGS/ObjectSuffix

  Put here the object-suffix (INCLUDING THE '.') you want to
  use for your objects. Recommended is '.o'. This is used to create a
  object-name which will replace the %o in a commandlist.

@endnode

@node "Dependant" "EZMake/Dependant"

GLOBAL SETTINGS/Dependant=Allways

  When this box is checked ALL sources are compiled when
  pressing @{"MAKE" LINK "bt_make"}. It does not matter what the compile-
  settings are, except when it's 'NEVER', then it won't be compiled.
  
@endnode


